			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First off, Joebwan:  You are level 19.  You are not even an illusionist yet.  I don't understand why you think you should have all the illusions available to you already that an endgame character in eq1  had.  It might be tough to accept, but level 19 is rather low.
<br />

<br />
Secondly, enchanters are important in groups still.  Perhaps not pre-20, but I have never had any trouble finding a group with my 29 coercer.  At higher levels (err, mid range levels as it may be) mobs just do too much damage for the healer to keep up if they are all free to attack.  The only solution then is to stack healers or get an enchanter type to keep damage flowing in at a reasonable rate.  Also, in the case the mob turns on the cleric, I often can fire a stun on it long before a tank could taunt it back, which has saved battles many times for me.  
<br />

<br />
One last point:  someone mentioned adds aren't a problem because of the new grouped encounter system.  This is not always true.  If you are fighting in an area where things are kos such as nek forest there is a very good chance someone will catch an exrta mob, be it the puller running back or something popping or just dumb groupmembers.  I don't think an hour of playing has gone by where I didn't have to keep a group of adds in check.
<br />

<br />
I do have some complaints about the chanter class, such as aoe mez being broken if one mob is attacked, but overall I think the class has it's place and you all need to play past the first fifth of the game (relative time invested) to be able to make any sort of sweeping judgement like you have.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
