			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Coercers do get a charm.  It lasts 30 seconds, you can't move and it breaks when it's hit.  It seems more of a CC spell than an offensive spell currently by all reports.
<br />

<br />
Another difference between the 2 is that by level 40, coercers will have 1 single target mez and 1 AoE mez (which does have uses despite what many might tell you).  Illusionists will have 2 single target mez's and 1 AoE mez.
<br />

<br />
Coercers have much stronger single target DD's, illusionists have much stronger AoE mez's.  All the casted mez's I've seen or heard about do not break mez's either, so you can mez bosses out of a pull and AE the rest without worry.
<br />

<br />
Yes, we are definately needed for adds.  Adds happen frequently, we just don't mez on most pulls, we mez when we get adds.  Adds become more frequent at higher levels.  I also mez when it's a 2 mob pull, single up arrow mobs still hurt.
<br />

<br />
Currently at 38, I can turn into human, half elf, dwarf and barbarian.  Later I'll get a Gnoll form too.
<br />

<br />
Anyways, it's not a bad class, just not as all powerfull as EQ1 enchanters.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
